<div id="invite_body">
<p>
<em>
  <a href="register">Sign up to judge/steward on the web!</a>
</em>
</p>
<p>
The Indiana State Fair Brewers Cup is one of the largest competitions
in the country with approximately 1000 professional and amateur
entries.  BJCP judges, professional brewers and BJCP apprentices
(those who have taken the test) are welcomed and encouraged to judge
at this year&#8217;s competition.  Judging will take place
on <strong>Friday, July 8th,</strong> and <strong>Saturday, July
9th,</strong> at the Farm Bureau Building on the Indiana State
Fairgrounds.  This is a BJCP-sanctioned competition, so points will be
awarded.  We also pay a small stipend to offset travel expenses to
professional brewers and BJCP judges.  Judges who travel at least 50
miles one way and judge at least two sessions will receive a $100
stipend.  Local judges will be paid $12.50 per session.  We provide
meals during the judging and you are welcome to stay for the Awards
Reception on Saturday evening.
</p>
<p>
We have arranged for a special rate of $69/night at
the <a href="http://martenhousehotel.com/">Marten House Hotel</a>.
You may also want to consider one of our downtown hotels.  The
Indianapolis downtown is safe, vibrant, and home to two brewpubs
(<a href="http://www.theram.com/indiana/indianapolis.shtml">RAM</a>
and <a href="http://www.rockbottom.com/indianapolis-downtown">Rock
Bottom</a>), two breweries
(<a href="http://www.sunkingbrewing.com/">Sun King</a>
and <a href="http://flat12.me/">Flat12 Bierwerks</a>), and many good
beer bars.  Indianapolis has many family-friendly venues, including a
fantastic <a href="http://www.indyzoo.com/">zoo</a> and a wonderful
<a href="http://www.childrensmuseum.org/">children's museum</a>.
</p>
<p>
The Brewers&#8217; Cup is a pre-fair event.  The fair takes place a
few weeks later.
</p>
